==Trivia==
*In the comics, Quentin Beck was a visual effects artist who wanted to make a name for himself in the film industry. Due to lack of recognition, Beck realized that his expertise in illusions could make him an effective supervillain, choosing his identity of '''Mysterio'''. Also, he was one of the founding members of [[Spider-Man]]'s recurrent group of enemies, the [[w:c:marvel:Sinister Six|Sinister Six]] alongside [[Vulture]], [[Doctor Octopus]], [[Sandman]], and [[Electro]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*Mysterio in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the first live-action incarnation of the character.
**Mysterio was originally intended to appear as a villain, played by [[Bruce Campbell]], in the canceled film ''{{WPS|Spider-Man 4}}'', part of [[Sam Raimi]]'s ''Spider-Man'' franchise.
**[[Sony Pictures Entertainment]] had announced plans for a film centered around Mysterio for their cinematic {{WPS|Sony's Spider-Man Universe}} by June 2017,<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-homecoming-how-sony-learned-cede-control-marvel-1015408 How Sony Learned to Cede Control to Marvel on 'Spider-Man: Homecoming']</ref> before the character was used in the MCU.
*Mysterio's actions in ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]'' are similar to his origins in the comics. In the comics, Mysterio is a former special effects man for movies, who wanted to ruin [[Spider-Man]]'s reputation by framing him for crimes and then defeat him as a new superhero. In the film, Mysterio is a former employee of Tony Stark, who wants to replace the fallen hero as "the next Iron Man," using his illusions of the Elementals to stage his debut. Screenwriters [[Erik Sommers]] and [[Chris McKenna]] thus had to deal with the challenge of updating Mysterio for the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] in the post-''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' era.<ref name="Mysterio Skrull?">[http://collider.com/spider-man-far-from-home-interview-erik-sommers-chris-mckenna/ ‘Spider-Man: Far from Home’ Writers on Mysterio, Those Credits Scenes, and Following ‘Endgame’]</ref>
*[[Matt Damon]] reportedly turned down the role of Quentin Beck before [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] was cast.<ref>[https://superbromovies.com/2018/03/30/matt-damon-turns-down-villain-role-in-sequel-to-spider-man-homecoming/ MATT DAMON Turns Down Villain Role In Sequel To ‘SPIDER-MAN: HOMECOMING’]</ref> Damon previously portrayed [[Loki (Asgardian Actor)|an actor]] playing [[Loki]] in ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]''.
**{{WPS|Matt Smith (actor)|Matt Smith}}, {{WPS|Andrew Scott (actor)|Andrew Scott}}, and {{WPS|Colin Farrell}} were also considered for the role of Mysterio.
***Gyllenhall himself had previously been considered for the role of [[Doctor Strange]].
*Early versions of the story of ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]'' had Mysterio's status as a villain revealed from the beginning, being an out-and-out villain that Spider-Man and [[Nick Fury]] would chase around all [[Europe]] as he pulled off the [[Elementals]] threat. However, as Mysterio dealt so much in deception, [[Chris McKenna]] and [[Erik Sommers]] accepted that it was sort of natural that Mysterio's ruse would lead to a story structure where his entire identity was completely misleading.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/09/movies/spider-man-far-from-home-screenwriters-twists.html ‘Spider-Man: Far From Home’: The Screenwriters Explain the Twists]</ref> Another early idea involved Mysterio actually being a [[Skrull]], but it was dropped.<ref name="Mysterio Skrull?"/>
*When asked if Mysterio died at the end of ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]'', [[Jon Watts]] didn't rule out the possibility of Mysterio surviving by responding "''It's Mysterio, so who knows?''" yet commenting that for him, Mysterio seemed pretty dead.<ref>[https://www.slashfilm.com/spider-man-far-from-home-spoiler-interview/ ‘Spider-Man: Far From Home’ Spoilers: Director Jon Watts on the Post-Credits Scene, the Song He Wrote for the Film, and More [Interview]]</ref> Producer [[Amy Pascal]], when asked the same question, responded "''You don't know''".<ref>[https://comicbook.com/marvel/2019/07/07/spider-man-far-from-home-mysterio-multiverse-dead-alive-mcu/ Spider-Man: Far From Home Director Breaks Down Mysterio, Major MCU Ties]</ref> [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] also commented that for him, Mysterio is "''a dead man''".<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTCFhiNMKFI Jake Gyllenhaal, Tom Sturridge, & Carrie Cracknell: "Broadway's Sea Wall / A Life" | Talks at Google]</ref>
*In scrapped concept art for ''[[Spider-Man: No Way Home]]'', Mysterio is seen battling [[Doctor Strange]] during the [[Battle at Liberty Island]]. Writer [[Chris McKenna]] indicated that it was an alternate version of Mysterio, "''When you open up the [[Multiverse]], you get a lot of conversations where anything can happen.''"<ref>[https://comicbookmovie.com/spider-man/no_way_home/spider-man-no-way-home-writer-addresses-that-mysterio-vs-doctor-strange-concept-art-from-the-movie-a192237 SPIDER-MAN: NO WAY HOME Writer Addresses That Mysterio Vs. Doctor Strange Concept Art From The Movie]</ref>
*[[James Cox]], [[James Harris]], [[Corbett McAllister]] and [[Timothy Eulich]] were stunt doubles for [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] in the role of Mysterio.
*[[James Payton]] was a stand-in for [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] in the role of Mysterio.

